				<Placemark>
					<name>Ivato International Airport and boneyard</name>
					<description>Joint military and civilian airport. North Western field seems to be the same from
 https://forum.keypublishing.com/showthread.php?125091-Small-Air-Forces-Thread-16/page14 
and looks like a boneyard .https://www.dc3dakotahunter.com/blog/madagascar-boneyard-tragic-end-of-c-47s-mig-21s-and-antonovs/
 MiG, Douglas and  An-26 of the Madagascan Aeronaval Force can be seen at this airport in several image results when Madagascan Air Force is searched. 
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ivato_International_Airport</description>
					<LookAt>
						<gx:TimeStamp><when>2017-10-07</when>
</gx:TimeStamp>
						<gx:ViewerOptions>
							<gx:option name="historicalimagery"></gx:option>
