				<Folder>
					<name>Beja Air Base (Base Aérea de Beja)</name>
					<Placemark>
						<name>Base Aérea de Beja (Beja Air Base)</name>
						<description>Beja Air Base (Portuguese: Base Aérea de Beja; IATA: BYJ, ICAO: LPBJ), designated as Air Base No. 11 (Portuguese: Base Aérea Nº 11, BA11) is one of the most important military airbases in Portugal.The base is home to two training squadrons, one helicopter squadron and one maritime patrol squadron.

103 Sqn. &quot;Caracóis&quot; (Snails) — complementary flying training and operational transition training.
- Dassault/Dornier Alpha Jet (1993—present)
552 Sqn. &quot;Zangões&quot; (Drones) — tactical air transport operations and complementary flying training in helicopters.
- Sud Aviation SE.3160 Alouette III
601 Sqn. &quot;Lobos&quot; (Wolves) — maritime patrol squadron.
- Lockheed P-3C CUP+ Orion</description>
