				<Folder>
					<name>Montijo Air Base (Base Aérea de Montijo)</name>
					<Placemark>
						<name>Base Aérea de Montijo (Montijo Air Base)</name>
						<description>Base Aérea de Montijo (Montijo Air Base) is home to three transport squadrons and one helicopter search and rescue squadron and provides logistic support to the Portuguese Navy&apos;s helicopters based there.

Portuguese Air Force:
501 Sqn. &quot;Bisontes&quot; (Bisons) — tactical transport squadron
-3 C-130H Hercules (1977—present)
-3 C-130H-30 Hercules (2 H2 and 1 H3)

502 Sqn. &quot;Elefantes&quot; (Elephants) — tactical and general transport squadron
-EADS CASA C-295 (2009—current)

504 Sqn. &quot;Linces&quot; (Lynxes) — VIP and MEDEVAC transport squadron
-Dassault Falcon 50 (1989—current)

751 Sqn. &quot;Pumas&quot; (Pumas) — search and rescue squadron
-AW101 Merlin (2006–today)

Portuguese Navy:
Esquadrilha de Helicópteros da Marinha (Navy Helicopter Squadron)
-AgustaWestland Super Lynx Mk.95</description>
